TRANSLA TJONS.

II.

Nymphs and Shepherds, dance no more

By sandy Ladon‘s lilied bankS, On old Lycaeus or Cyllene hoar

Trip no more in twilight ranks: Though Erymanth your loss deplore

A better soil shall give ye thanks.

From the stony Maenalus Bring your flocks and live with us:

Here ye shall have greater grace

To serve the lady of this place; Though Syrinx your Pan’s mistress were, Yet Syrinx well might wait on her: Such a rural queen All Arcadia hath not seen.
